### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

I'm using Angular 15. Created a new Angular component as follows.
```
import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-foo',
  templateUrl: './foo.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./foo.component.css']
})
export class FooComponent {

}
```
So far no problem, When I implement the OnInit interface,
```
import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-foo',
  templateUrl: './foo.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./foo.component.css']
})
export class FooComponent implements OnInit {

  ngOnInit(): void {

  }

}
```
I'm getting the following error.

> Class is using Angular features but is not decorated. Please add an explicit Angular decorator.(-992007)

